### Phase 2 — manual QA collection
# Covers the full Phase 2 happy path:
#   auth two users → PUT watch list → PUT broadcast list → WebSocket match event.
#
# IntelliJ HTTP Client: select the "dev" environment from http-client.env.json.
# VS Code REST Client: fill in @watchToken / @broadcastToken / @wsBaseUrl manually.
#
# ── End-to-end walkthrough ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   1. Start the server:
#        cd server && ./gradlew bootRun
#
#   2. Authenticate the watcher (free user):
#        a. Run "Send OTP — watcher" below.
#        b. Copy the OTP from the [DEV] console log.
#        c. Run "Verify OTP — watcher"; paste accessToken into @watchToken below.
#
#   3. Authenticate the broadcaster (paid user):
#        a. Run "Send OTP — broadcaster" using a different phone number.
#        b. Run "Verify OTP — broadcaster"; paste accessToken into @broadcastToken.
#        c. Run the checkout flow from phase1.http with @broadcastToken so the
#           broadcaster has woleh.place.broadcast.  Verify with
#           "GET /subscription/status — broadcaster".
#
#   4. Run "PUT watch list — happy path" to set the watcher's places.
#
#   5. Open the WebSocket connection for the watcher (§5 below) in IntelliJ's
#      WS client (or wscat / websocat).  Observe the first heartbeat frame:
#        {"type":"heartbeat","data":"ping"}
#
#   6. Run "PUT broadcast list — happy path" with a list that shares a stop.
#      The watcher's WS session should immediately receive:
#        {"type":"match","data":{"matchedNames":["madina"],"counterpartyUserId":"<broadcasterId>","kind":"broadcast_to_watch"}}
#
# ── Variables ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@baseUrl        = {{baseUrl}}
@wsBaseUrl      = {{wsBaseUrl}}
@watchPhone     = {{watchPhone}}
@broadcastPhone = {{broadcastPhone}}
@watchToken     = PASTE_WATCHER_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
@broadcastToken = PASTE_BROADCASTER_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

###############################################################################
# 1. Authentication — watcher (free user, woleh.place.watch only)
###############################################################################

### Send OTP — watcher
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneE164": "{{watchPhone}}"
}

### Verify OTP — watcher  →  paste accessToken into @watchToken above
# Replace 123456 with the OTP from the [DEV] console log.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneE164": "{{watchPhone}}",
  "otp": "123456"
}

###############################################################################
# 2. Authentication — broadcaster (must subscribe to paid plan for broadcast access)
###############################################################################

### Send OTP — broadcaster
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneE164": "{{broadcastPhone}}"
}

### Verify OTP — broadcaster  →  paste accessToken into @broadcastToken above
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneE164": "{{broadcastPhone}}",
  "otp": "123456"
}

### GET /subscription/status — broadcaster (confirms tier=paid and woleh.place.broadcast is present)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/subscription/status
Authorization: Bearer {{broadcastToken}}

###############################################################################
# 3. Watch list  (GET + PUT /api/v1/me/places/watch)
###############################################################################

### GET watch list — empty on first visit
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/watch
Authorization: Bearer {{watchToken}}

### PUT watch list — happy path (expects 200, normalized + deduped list returned)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/watch
Authorization: Bearer {{watchToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "names": ["Madina", "Lapaz", "Legon"]
}

### GET watch list — confirm saved (expects names in insertion order)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/watch
Authorization: Bearer {{watchToken}}

### PUT watch list — case-variant duplicate deduped silently
# "MADINA" and "Madina" normalize to "madina"; only "Madina" (first) is kept.
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/watch
Authorization: Bearer {{watchToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "names": ["Madina", "MADINA", "Lapaz"]
}

### PUT watch list — exceeds free-tier limit of 5 names (expects 403 OVER_LIMIT)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/watch
Authorization: Bearer {{watchToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "names": ["A", "B", "C", "D", "E", "F"]
}

### PUT watch list — empty name (expects 400 VALIDATION_ERROR)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/watch
Authorization: Bearer {{watchToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "names": ["Madina", "   "]
}

### PUT watch list — clear list (expects 200, empty names array)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/watch
Authorization: Bearer {{watchToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "names": []
}

### PUT watch list — no auth (expects 401 UNAUTHORIZED)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/watch
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "names": ["Madina"]
}

###############################################################################
# 4. Broadcast list  (GET + PUT /api/v1/me/places/broadcast)
###############################################################################

### GET broadcast list — empty on first visit
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/broadcast
Authorization: Bearer {{broadcastToken}}

### PUT broadcast list — happy path (expects 200, ordered list returned)
# Run step 3's "PUT watch list — happy path" first so there is an overlapping stop.
# After this request the watcher's WS session should receive a match event for "madina".
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/broadcast
Authorization: Bearer {{broadcastToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "names": ["MADINA", "Kaneshie", "Circle"]
}

### GET broadcast list — confirm saved in order
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/broadcast
Authorization: Bearer {{broadcastToken}}

### PUT broadcast list — duplicate normalized name (expects 400 VALIDATION_ERROR)
# "Madina" and "madina " normalize to the same form — broadcast list rejects duplicates.
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/broadcast
Authorization: Bearer {{broadcastToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "names": ["Madina", "Kaneshie", "madina "]
}

### PUT broadcast list — free user lacks permission (expects 403 PERMISSION_DENIED)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/broadcast
Authorization: Bearer {{watchToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "names": ["Madina"]
}

### PUT broadcast list — empty name (expects 400 VALIDATION_ERROR)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/broadcast
Authorization: Bearer {{broadcastToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "names": ["Madina", ""]
}

### PUT broadcast list — clear list
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/broadcast
Authorization: Bearer {{broadcastToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "names": []
}

###############################################################################
# 5. WebSocket — /ws/v1/transit
#
# IntelliJ HTTP Client supports WebSocket natively (WEBSOCKET keyword).
# Alternative tools: wscat, websocat, or the browser DevTools WS console.
#
# Connect watcher:
#   wscat -c "ws://localhost:8080/ws/v1/transit?access_token=<watchToken>"
#
# Expected first frame (within 15 s):
#   {"type":"heartbeat","data":"ping"}
#
# After "PUT broadcast list — happy path" (§4) you should see a match frame:
#   {"type":"match","data":{"matchedNames":["madina"],"counterpartyUserId":"<broadcasterId>","kind":"broadcast_to_watch"}}
###############################################################################

### Connect watcher to /ws/v1/transit (IntelliJ WS client)
# Select this request in IntelliJ and click "Open WebSocket connection".
WEBSOCKET {{wsBaseUrl}}/ws/v1/transit?access_token={{watchToken}}

### Connect broadcaster to /ws/v1/transit (receive match on watch PUT, see §6)
WEBSOCKET {{wsBaseUrl}}/ws/v1/transit?access_token={{broadcastToken}}

### WS — missing token (expects HTTP 403; connection upgrade is rejected)
WEBSOCKET {{wsBaseUrl}}/ws/v1/transit

### WS — invalid token (expects HTTP 403)
WEBSOCKET {{wsBaseUrl}}/ws/v1/transit?access_token=not.a.valid.jwt

###############################################################################
# 6. Match event flow — the full end-to-end sequence
#
# Run these requests in order with BOTH watcher and broadcaster WS sessions open.
# Each step references the request defined in §3 and §4 above.
###############################################################################

### Step A: Restore watcher's watch list (contains "Madina" → normalizes to "madina")
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/watch
Authorization: Bearer {{watchToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "names": ["Madina", "Lapaz", "Legon"]
}

### Step B: PUT broadcaster's broadcast list (overlaps "Madina" → match fires)
# With the watcher's WS open, the watcher receives:
#   {"type":"match","data":{"matchedNames":["madina"],"counterpartyUserId":"<broadcasterId>","kind":"broadcast_to_watch"}}
# The broadcaster also receives (if their WS is open):
#   {"type":"match","data":{"matchedNames":["madina"],"counterpartyUserId":"<watcherId>","kind":"broadcast_to_watch"}}
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/broadcast
Authorization: Bearer {{broadcastToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "names": ["MADINA", "Kaneshie", "Circle"]
}

### Step C: PUT broadcaster's broadcast list with NO overlap (no match event expected)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/broadcast
Authorization: Bearer {{broadcastToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "names": ["Kaneshie", "Circle"]
}

### Step D: Clear watcher's watch list (no match events fired for empty list)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/watch
Authorization: Bearer {{watchToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "names": []
}

### Step E: PUT broadcaster's list again — watcher has empty list, no match expected
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/places/broadcast
Authorization: Bearer {{broadcastToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "names": ["MADINA", "Kaneshie"]
}
